I guess I’ll wait 30 years and try again.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SlVOLaN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CamelEnamel]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Just a thought ....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/quT4cK6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1If49sc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/quT4cK6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Healthcare Worker Memes posted in timely night-shift fashion</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nl1lZCI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YIckDDv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>AMA- signing out against medical advice.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vyVCK17.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3Vuf2QE.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I'm looking at you, Geraldine.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FHeVBz2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/H0pQVqv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>GCS- Glasgow Coma Scale. It is an assessment for a person's level of consciousness, scored 3-15 based on three types of stimuli (eye-opening, verbal response, and motor response). A score of 16/15 probably means you can smell colors</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zNPG8Ze.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nQ10PeK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/d5oZOBY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sundowning- a phenomenon in which elderly people become drastically confused at night. They  may be pleasant and oriented during the day but at night they are confused, disoriented, and impulsive. Like gremlins!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/H8H0CW4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/InQGf2a.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1CuVFTl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2PDp5gf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rp6otFu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ohq1ina.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And nurses be like... damn, this fucker again</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uQIq1an.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Still stings.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bcftwHx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>An ideal blood pressure is 120/80. A low blood pressure causes concern that blood is not circulating the body enough to provide sustenance for tissue. MAP (mean arterial pressure) is the diastolic (80) x2 plus the systolic (120) and divided by 3, equaling 93
The MAP needs to be greater than 65 for the body to be perfused adequately.

Someone with a pressure of 79/58 would likely end up on pressors (medications to raise blood pressure like norepinephrine)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/d26aTlI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/X7doZJg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rxUrBdu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OGm9R9W.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A lot of unprocessed trauma.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/k90BsOW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DrbefUF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/m605ZVC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HcmtRhq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wIvtCYg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Damnit Geraldine!!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qHPQVcp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6cIKkFJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Love it when those horrible patients leave and stop wasting resources.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/znfrtDa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Kick rocks. Last week I put an 18g in the foot of a drug addict writhing around in a stretcher vomiting.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KVQmBGV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FF9qQJ9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6H5W0Oj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bij6HdI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Foreign body removal ;) this one's for you  emergency, colorectal and general surgery</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MnaLTUT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cat Tax
